  "directed": {
    "format": "rules-card very-big-rules-card",
    "title": "Directed",
    "subtitle": "Variation Keyword",
    "blocks": [
      "Directed Variations (or Directed effects of certain Tiered Variations), follow special rules:",
      "<span class='tooltip-list-item'>Once activated (or if it is Persistent and Perpetual), {{NAME}} may direct the power of the Variation each turn as an instant action.</span>",
      "<span class='tooltip-list-item'>Directing the Variation can (and usually does) target a character or object other than {{NAME}} {{himself}}. The initial target may be chosen as part of a Controlled Variation's activation roll. If the Variation is Persistent and Perpetual, it always requires an instant action to choose a target. If the Variation is Involuntary (or Persistent and Toggled), and {{NAME}} used an instant action to activate it, the target may be chosen as part of that action; if the power triggered as a result of events outside {{NAME}}'s control, it requires an instant action to choose a target.</span>",
      "<span class='tooltip-list-item'>{{NAME}} may choose one new target each turn, as an instant action, which always requires a successful Scar Finesse roll. The maximum number of targets {{NAME}} may have under the influence of a Directed Variation at a time cannot exceed Scar Power. If {{he}} would exceed this target limit, the Variation's effects end on enough previous targets to bring {{him}} back within this limit.</span>",
      "<span class='tooltip-list-item'>A Directed Variation has a range of <strong>10/20/40</strong> meters. {{NAME}} suffers a penalty on the Scar Finesse roll if the target is at medium or long range or is obscured by concealment. Directed Variations cannot ordinarily penetrate cover.</span>",
      "<span class='tooltip-list-item'>Unless targeting a willing and aware target, the victim may make a reflexive Resistance + Supernatural Tolerance roll to contest the Variation's effects. Variations that are instead resisted by a target's Defense are not usually contested, too.</span>",
      "<span class='tooltip-list-item'>{{NAME}} may choose to target a Directed Variation while grappled, acting on {{his}} normal Initiative (instead of the highest Initiative among grappling parties). However, doing so forces {{him}} to automatically lose (achieve no successes on) the next contested grapple check; the Variation may only target participants in the grapple; and the Scar Finesse roll to direct the Variation suffers a &minus;2 penalty.</span>",
      "<span class='tooltip-list-item'>Certain Directed Variations have an Aura Deviation. In these cases, the Variation potentially affects all viable targets within short range other than {{NAME}} (whether friend or foe) and is not limited to a number of victims equal to Scar Power. {{NAME}} makes a single Scar Finesse roll, and each potential target makes a separate reflexive Resistance + Supernatural Tolerance roll to contest its effects. If successful, the victim cannot be affected by the aura during the current scene. The effects of the aura end immediately if the target is no longer within long range of {{NAME}} or moves behind cover, but moving within short range again triggers a fresh Scar Resistance roll to reapply the aura's effect. Concealment works in one of two ways, chosen at the time {{NAME}} develops the aura: Either concealment affords no protection at all, or it grants a bonus to all potential targets' Resistance + Supernatural Tolerance roll equal to the penalty the concealment would ordinarily impose on an attack roll (+1 for barely concealed, +2 for partially concealed, etc.).</span>"
    ],
    "source": {
      "book": "DtR",
      "page": 110
    }
  },
  "discrete": {
    "format": "rules-card",
    "title": "Discrete",
    "subtitle": "Variation Keyword",
    "blocks": [
      "The Variation only grants the specific abilities of its current Magnitude rating, and does not grant lower-Magnitude benefits. It can often be bought multiple times at different ratings to access those further capabilities.",
      "Most Discrete Variations cannot have their Magnitude temporarily increased or decreased by Adaptations or Scars. Exceptions to this will be noted in the Variation's description â€” however, in such a case, {{NAME}} must determine how the Variation functions at <em>every</em> available Magnitude at the time of purchase.",
      "Scars that would reduce the Magnitude of an active Discrete Variation instead cause the Variation to deactivate after a number of failed Scar Resistance rolls equal to the Variation's Magnitude."
    ],
    "source": {
      "book": "DtR",
      "page": 110
    }
  },
