  "extendedAction": {
    "format": "rules-card big-rules-card",
    "title": "Extended Action",
    "subtitle": "Action Time",
    "blocks": [
      "An extended action is resolved with multiple rolls made over a period of time and, as such, is not usually an option in action scenes unless otherwise noted.",
      "The Storyteller determines how many total successes are required to succeed at an extended action. The Storyteller also determines the <strong>interval</strong> between rolls.",
      "Once you determine these factors, make a number of rolls, counting up the total number of successes across all your rolls. If you earn the required number of successes before you run out of time, you accomplish your goal.",
      "You can make a total number of rolls equal to your base dice pool for the action, before factoring in any modifiers.",
      "<strong>Roll Results</strong>",
      "<span class='tooltip-list-item'><strong>Success:</strong> Add the successes earned on the roll to your running total. Work with the Storyteller to determine what steps you have taken towards your goal.</span>",
      "<span class='tooltip-list-item'><strong>Exceptional Success:</strong> Choose one: reduce the total number of successes required by your Skill dots; reduce the interval between each roll by a quarter; or apply the effects of an exceptional success to the entire action when you complete your goal.</span>",
      "<span class='tooltip-list-item'><strong>Failure:</strong> You face a setback. The Storyteller offers you a choice: Take a Condition of their choice, or abandon the action. You can offer a different Condition if you think it makes sense. If you refuse or cannot agree on a Condition, you lose all accumulated successes.</span>",
      "<span class='tooltip-list-item'><strong>Dramatic Failure:</strong> Lose all accumulated successes. In addition, the first roll on a subsequent attempt suffers a &minus;2 die penalty..</span>",
    ],
    "source": {
      "book": "DtR",
      "page": 189
    }
  },
  "reflexiveAction": {
    "format": "rules-card",
    "title": "Reflexive Action",
    "subtitle": "Action Time",
    "blocks": [
      "A reflexive action takes no appreciable time or effort, and resolves in a single roll, or may not require a roll at all.",
      "In an action scene, you can take reflexive actions on other characters' turns, and reflexive actions don't take up your turn.",
      "Contesting someone else's action is always reflexive."
    ],
    "source": {
      "book": "DtR",
      "page": 189
    }
  },
  "resisted": {
    "format": "rules-card",
    "title": "Resisted",
    "subtitle": "Action Opposition",
    "blocks": [
      "A resisted action is opposed by one of your target's Resistance Attributes (Stamina, Resolve or Composure), or their Defense.",
      "Subtract the appropriate trait from your dice pool, then roll and calculate results as normal."
    ],
    "source": {
      "book": "DtR",
      "page": 189
    }
  },
  "contested": {
    "format": "rules-card",
    "title": "Contested",
    "subtitle": "Action Opposition",
    "blocks": [
      "A contested action is opposed by a reflexive roll made by your target.",
      "Calculate your dice pool and roll results as normal. Then, your target rolls a dice pool specified by how they contest the action.",
      "If your total successes exceed the target's, your action succeeds; if their total successes exceed yours, your action fails.",
      "If you and your target roll the same number of successes, both of you reroll the same pools until someone comes out on top."
    ],
    "source": {
      "book": "DtR",
      "page": 189
    }
  },
